<TITLE> Tarique gets bail in twin extortion cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 4 (bdnews24.com)The High Court Tuesday granted bail to former prime minister Khaleda Zia's son Tarique Rahman in twin extortion cases and suspended their proceedings in the trial court. The High Court bench of Justice Shah Abu Nayeem Mominur Rahman and Justice Shahidul Islam granted the bail to Tarique, now detained in jail, after he filed two writ petitions. Tarique will not be freed as he faces a raft of other cases. Tarique was arrested on March 8. An Al-Amin Construction official filed an extortion case against Tarique with Gulshan Police Station on May 4, accusing him of collecting Tk 4.89 crore in extortion. Earlier on March 27, Reza Constructions owner Aftabuddin Khan filed a Tk 1.32 crore extortion case against Tarique with Kafrul Police Station. Senior advocate Habibul Islam Bhuiyan and barrister Mahbubuddin Khokan took part in the hearing on the writ petitions on behalf of Tarique. The government was represented by deputy attorney general Syeda Afsar Jahan. bdnew
